<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Pet Tracker Usage Guide</h1>

  <p class="text-base mb-6">This guide provides detailed instructions on how to use the key features of Pet Tracker.</p>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div class="container border-2 border-grayishBlue rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">User Account</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Your user account is the central hub for managing your pets and tracking their dietary.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Creating an Account</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4">
        <li><strong>Sign Up:</strong> Navigate to the "Get Started" page.</li>
        <li>There are 4 ways to create account: </li>
          <div class="font-semibold ml-4 mt-1">
            Enter Your Details (App's Form): Provide your email address and a secure password.
          </div>
          <div class="font-semibold ml-4 mt-1">
            Google/GitHub: Using Google or GitHub to create account.
          </div>
          <div class="font-semibold ml-4 mt-1">
            Line: Using Line to create account.
          </div>
          <div class="font-semibold text-softBlue text-sm ml-4 mt-1 mb-3">Using line to sign up, the page will redirect to the form for filling email and password</div>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Register:</strong> Click the "Sign Up" button to create your account.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Signing In</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4">
        <li><strong>Sign In:</strong> Go to the "Sign In" page.</li>
        <li><strong>Enter Your Credentials:</strong> Enter your email and password.</li>
        <li><strong>Access Your Account:</strong> Click the "Sign In" button to access your dashboard.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Third-Party Sign-In</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">You can also sign in using a third-party provider for a more streamlined experience.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Timezone</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">App will automatically set your local timezone during your account settings to ensure all tracking data is accurate.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="container border-2 border-grayishBlue rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">Pet Management</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">The "Pets" section allows you to create and manage profiles for each of your pets.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Adding a Pet</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4">
        <li><strong>Go to Pets:</strong> Navigate to the "User's Cats" section from the main menu.</li>
        <li><strong>New Pet:</strong> Click the "Add A Cat" button.</li>
        <li><strong>Enter Pet Details:</strong> Fill in your pet's name, species, and other relevant information.</li>
        <li><strong>Save:</strong> Click "Add A Cat" to save the profile.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Viewing and Editing Pets</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">Navigate to the "User's Cats" section from the main menu. The dropdown menu will show all the pets' name. Click on a pet's name to see their detailed profile.</li>
        <li><strong>Edit:</strong> From the pet's profile page, click "Edit pet's name Porfile" to update their information.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

     <div class="container border-2 border-grayishBlue rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">Dry Food Storage</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">The "Dry Food Storage" feature helps you keep track of your pet's dry food inventory.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Adding Dry Food</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4">
        <li><strong>Go to Dry Foods:</strong> Navigate to the "Dry Foods" section.</li>
        <li><strong>New Dry Food:</strong> Click the "New Dry Food" button.</li>
        <li><strong>Enter Food Details:</strong> Provide the brand, name, and quantity of the dry food.</li>
        <li><strong>Save:</strong> Click "Create Dry Food" to add it to your inventory.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Managing Inventory</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
        <li><strong>View:</strong> See a list of all your dry foods and their current quantities.</li>
        <li><strong>Edit:</strong> Update the details or quantity of a dry food entry.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Remove a dry food entry from your inventory.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

     <div class="container border-2 border-grayishBlue rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">Trackers</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Trackers are used to log your pet's daily activities, such as feeding times, walks, and health observations.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Creating a Tracker</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4">
        <li><strong>Go to Trackers:</strong> Navigate to the "Trackers" section.</li>
        <li><strong>New Tracker:</strong> Click the "New Tracker" button.</li>
        <li><strong>Select Pet:</strong> Choose the pet you want to create a tracker for.</li>
        <li><strong>Enter Details:</strong> Fill in the activity details, such as the type of activity, time, and any notes.</li>
        <li><strong>Save:</strong> Click "Create Tracker" to log the activity.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Importing Trackers from CSV</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">For bulk data entry, you can import trackers from a CSV file.</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4">
        <li><strong>Go to Trackers:</strong> Navigate to the "Trackers" section.</li>
        <li><strong>Import CSV:</strong> Click the "Import CSV" button.</li>
        <li><strong>Choose File:</strong> Select the CSV file you want to import.</li>
        <li><strong>Upload:</strong> Click "Import" to upload and process the file.</li>
      </ol>

      <p class="mb-2">The CSV file should have the following columns:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
        <li><code>pet_name</code></li>
        <li><code>activity_type</code></li>
        <li><code>activity_time</code></li>
        <li><code>notes</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
